      "target": {
        "kind": "pull_request",
        "title": "fix(telegram): prevent silent misparse of multi-colon delivery targets",
        "body": "## Summary\n\n`parseTelegramTarget` uses two regex parsers in order:\n1. `^(.+?):topic:(\\\\d+)$` — explicit `:topic:` marker (preferred)\n2. `^(.+):(\\\\d+)$` — legacy colon format\n\nBoth had the same bug: greedy/non-greedy `.+` would silently absorb colons in malformed multi-colon inputs, embedding `:topic:N` or other colon-separated segments into chatId.\n\n**Fix:** Apply `[^:]+` to both regexes so neither parser ever accepts a chatId containing colons. Malformed inputs fall through to the honest full-string fallback instead of silently producing a wrong chatId with corrupted session keys and routing.\n\n## Real behavior proof\n\n### Behavior or issue addressed\n**Before fix:**\n- `parseTelegramTarget(\\\"chatId:topic:42:99\\\")` → `chatId: \\\"chatId:topic:42\\\"`, `messageThreadId: 99` ← `:topic:42` residue embedded in chatId\n- `parseTelegramTarget(\\\"a:b:topic:42\\\")` → `chatId: \\\"a:b\\\"`, `messageThreadId: 42` ← chatId wrongly trimmed\n\n**Downstream impact:**\n- Session key: `\\\"-100:topic:42:topic:99\\\"` (duplicate `:topic:`) — creates separate session from same chat with correct target\n- ChatType: `\\\"unknown\\\"` (because `\\\"-100:topic:42\\\"` is not pure numeric) — wrong for numeric group IDs\n- Outbound routing: Telegram API gets wrong chatId → \\\"chat not found\\\"\n\n### Real environment tested\n- Local checkout: Linux, Node 22.21.0, `pnpm test`\n- Direct ESM import verification of `parseTelegramTarget`\n\n### Evidence after fix\n```\n══════════════════════════════════════════════════════\n  PR #97823 — Telegram multi-colon misparse fix\n══════════════════════════════════════════════════════\n\n── Bug: colon-form multi-colon ──\n  ✅ colon-form rejected\n  ✅ chatId is NOT the buggy partial \\\"chatId:topic:42\\\"\n── Bug: topic-form multi-colon ──\n  ✅ topic-form rejected\n  ✅ no silent threadId parse for topic-form\n── Bug: deeply nested ──\n  ✅ deeply nested rejected\n── Regression: valid formats ──\n  ✅ plain numeric chatId\n  ✅ @username\n  ✅ chatId:topic:N\n  ✅ chatId:N\n  ✅ non-numeric suffix\n  ✅ prefix stripping\n  ✅ threadId=0\n── Session key integrity ──\n  ✅ old session key would have duplicate :topic:\n  ✅ new session key has no duplicate :topic:\n══════════════════════════════════════════════════════\n  14 passed, 0 failed\n══════════════════════════════════════════════════════\n```\n\n### Exact steps run after this patch\n```bash\n$ node pr-proof.mjs\n  14 passed, 0 failed\n\n$ npx oxlint extensions/telegram/src/targets.ts extensions/telegram/src/targets.test.ts\n  Exit: 0\n\n$ pnpm test extensions/telegram/src/targets.test.ts\n  Test Files  1 passed (1)\n      Tests  45 passed (45)\n```\n\n### What was not tested\n- Full E2E integration with live Telegram API (requires bot token)\n\n## Tests and validation\n- `pnpm test extensions/telegram/src/targets.test.ts` — 45 passed (5 new tests: colon-form multi-colon, topic-form multi-colon, deeply nested, plus 2 format regression guards)\n- `npx oxlint` — no lint issues\n- Manual terminal-visible verification with `node pr-proof.mjs` — 14/14 assertions pass\n- PR changes: 2 files, +14 -3 (source +6 -3, tests +9 -0)\n\n## Risk checklist\n- [x] **User-facing behavior change**: No. Valid formats (`chatId`, `chatId:topic:N`, `chatId:N`) produce identical results. Only malformed multi-colon inputs change from silent corruption to honest fallback.\n- [x] **Backward compatible**: 100%.\n- [x] **Plugin SDK surface change**: No. Internal parser change only.\n- [x] **Config/doc surface change**: No.\n- [x] **New dependency**: No.\n- [x] **Both suffix parsers (topic + colon) guarded**: Yes.",
        "branch": "fix/telegram-target-multiple-colon-misparse",
